IT STARTED BACK WHEN I WAS
ON A GIRLS' SOCCER TEAM.

231
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:54,867
<i>MY FAMILY OWNED A FLOWER SHOP.</i>
<i>IT WAS MY MOM'S WHOLE LIFE.</i>

232
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:57,367
MOM, I GOT TO GO
TO THE SOCCER MATCH.

233
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:59,367
THE GIRLS ARE COUNTING
ON ME.

234
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:01,367
DON'T TALK SO LOUD, DEAR.

235
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,367
THE FLOWERS
ARE VERY SENSITIVE.

236
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:05,367
BUT THIS MATCH IS
TO WIN THE TITLE.

237
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,867
SORA, YOU CAN'T GO

238
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:08,867
WITH YOUR KNEE INJURED
LIKE THAT.

239
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:10,867
BUT, MOM, MY LEG'S FINE.

240
00:10:10,900 --> 00:10:12,867
I'M SORRY. YOU CAN'T GO.

241
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:14,867
SIT DOWN.
WE NEED TO TALK.

242
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:17,367
I WANT YOU TO STOP
PLAYING SOCCER AND COME

243
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:19,533
TO WORK AT THE FLOWER SHOP
AFTER SCHOOL.

244
00:10:19,567 --> 00:10:20,867
DO WHAT?

245
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:23,867
I WON'T STOP PLAYING TO WORK
WITH SMELLY OLD FLOWERS.

246
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:25,200
I CAN'T BELIEVE

247
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:27,200
A DAUGHTER OF MINE
WOULD ACT THIS WAY.

248
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:28,700
MY DECISION IS FINAL.

249
00:10:28,733 --> 00:10:30,533
[ SOBBING ]

250
00:10:30,567 --> 00:10:33,833
WHY CAN'T YOU
UNDERSTAND ME?

251
00:10:33,867 --> 00:10:35,833
<i>I WALKED AROUND FOR HOURS.</i>

252
00:10:35,867 --> 00:10:38,000
<i>I FOUND MYSELF</i>
<i>AT THE SOCCER FIELD.</i>

253
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:40,000
<i>THE GAME HAD JUST FINISHED.</i>

254
00:10:40,033 --> 00:10:41,467
Matt: <i>WHAT HAPPENED?</i>

255
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:43,800
<i>WE LOST THE GAME 6 TO 3.</i>

256
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:47,733
<i>MY TEAMMATES WERE SO DEPRESSED</i>
<i>THAT THEY DIDN'T NOTICE ME</i>

257
00:10:47,767 --> 00:10:49,567
<i>WHEN THEY WALKED BY ME.</i>

258
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,733
<i>I FELT</i>
<i>LIKE I HAD LET THEM DOWN,</i>

259
00:10:51,767 --> 00:10:53,700
<i>LIKE IT WAS ALL MY FAULT.</i>

260
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:57,700
MY MOM SAID I HAD TO BE PART
OF THE FAMILY BUSINESS,

261
00:10:57,733 --> 00:10:59,367
NO QUESTIONS.

262
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,867
THAT'S HOW SHE IS.

263
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:03,800
IT'S LIKE IT'S THE ONLY THING
THAT'S IMPORTANT TO HER.

264
00:11:03,833 --> 00:11:05,633
SHE DOESN'T UNDERSTAND.

265
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:10,467
THAT'S WHY I KNOW
HE WASN'T LYING WHEN HE SAID

266
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:12,467
I GREW UP NOT KNOWING
WHAT LOVE IS.

267
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,533
STOP IT.

268
00:11:13,567 --> 00:11:14,600
LET GO!

269
00:11:14,633 --> 00:11:16,933
EVEN IF WHAT YOU SAID
IS TRUE,

270
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:20,067
YOU SHOULDN'T BELIEVE A WORD
FROM THAT LOSER DEMIDEVIMON.

271
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:23,167
HE'S JUST A CREEP
THAT'S TRYING TO HURT YOU.

272
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:24,833
[ CRYING ]

273
00:11:24,867 --> 00:11:27,500
WAIT, WAIT.
DON'T CRY, SORA.

274
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:34,941
DON'T CRY, SORA. MATT, HELP.
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO DO

275
00:11:34,941 --> 00:11:36,645
WITH HER WHEN SHE
STARTS BLUBBERING.

276
00:11:36,645 --> 00:11:39,578
JUST LET HER GO, TAI.
SHE'LL BE OKAY.

277
00:11:39,611 --> 00:11:42,078
BOY, MATT'S LIKE
A REAL GROWN-UP.

278
00:11:42,111 --> 00:11:44,745
NOW IF ONLY
HE WOULD CUT HIS HAIR.

279
00:11:44,778 --> 00:11:47,111
SORA, I FORGOT
TO THANK YOU.

280
00:11:47,145 --> 00:11:49,078
HUH?

281
00:11:49,111 --> 00:11:52,011
YOU TOLD US NOT TO EAT
THE MUSHROOMS, DIDN'T YOU?

282
00:11:52,045 --> 00:11:54,045
I WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR SAVING US.

283
00:11:54,078 --> 00:11:56,211
WE THOUGHT DEMIDEVIMON
WAS UP TO NO GOOD,

284
00:11:56,245 --> 00:11:58,545
SO WE KEPT OUT OF SIGHT
AND MADE SURE

285
00:11:58,578 --> 00:12:00,511
YOU GUYS
STAYED OUT OF TROUBLE.

286
00:12:00,545 --> 00:12:01,845
WE WERE EVEN THERE

287
00:12:01,878 --> 00:12:04,278
WHEN YOU GUYS WERE WORKING
IN THE RESTAURANT, MATT.

288
00:12:04,311 --> 00:12:05,378
HUH?

289
00:12:09,178 --> 00:12:12,111
I HAD NO IDEA.

290
00:12:12,145 --> 00:12:14,111
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO HIDE
FROM US.

291
00:12:14,145 --> 00:12:15,611
WE WERE ALL WORRIED.

292
00:12:15,645 --> 00:12:18,078
SORA JUST NEEDED TO BE ALONE
FOR A LITTLE WHILE,

293
00:12:18,111 --> 00:12:21,078
BUT SHE REALLY DIDN'T WANT
TO BE SEPARATED FROM YOU GUYS.

294
00:12:21,111 --> 00:12:23,545
PLEASE UNDERSTAND.

295
00:12:23,578 --> 00:12:26,245
SORA, I LIKE YOU.

296
00:12:26,278 --> 00:12:27,578
HUH?

297
00:12:27,611 --> 00:12:30,511
SO, PLEASE,
DON'T GO AWAY AGAIN.

298
00:12:30,545 --> 00:12:33,178
I DON'T LIKE
BEING AWAY FROM YOU.

299
00:12:33,211 --> 00:12:37,478
HA HA. WHEN YOU'RE AROUND,
I DON'T MISS MY MOM AS MUCH.

300
00:12:37,511 --> 00:12:40,078
T.K.

301
00:12:40,111 --> 00:12:41,411
[ SOBBING ]

302
00:12:41,445 --> 00:12:44,411
I'M SO, SO SORRY.

303
00:12:44,445 --> 00:12:47,078
Joe: HEY.

304
00:12:48,478 --> 00:12:50,811
HEY,
WHAT TOOK YOU GUYS SO LONG?

305
00:12:50,845 --> 00:12:52,811
Mimi: WELL, WE WOULD HAVE
BEEN HERE SOONER,

306
00:12:52,845 --> 00:12:54,811
